questions: can you provide me with some workshops that can help manage stress

Chat history: The user asked for stress management workshops, and the assistant recommended workshops like "Stress Better: Skills for Managing Stress" and "Building Social Confidence Group." The assistant also suggested the Cognitive-Behavioral Therapy (CBT) group for managing stress and anxiety. When the user inquired about other workshops, the assistant listed options like Eating Disorder Recovery Connections, Community Support for International Students, and Queer Community Connections. Manage stress, tame anxiety, and work on your well-being. This is a CBT (cognitive-behavioral therapy) group to learn how to better manage stress and anxiety. Topics covered include how to identify and change anxious thought patterns, reducing worry and avoidance, managing panic, improving sleep, and increasing well-being. Each week students will learn effective strategies that they can immediately apply to help tame anxiety.

Would you like to improve the quality of social interactions and the availability of social support? It combines an educational and support approach.
